===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|Balthasar|lang=la}}, equivalent of the English biblical [[Belshazzar]].  From Hebrew "bēlšaṣṣar", attested in the Tanakh and the Old Testament (Daniel, 5:1), from Akkadian "bēl-šarra-uṣṣur", literally "May Bel protect the king".

